    						vpon Earth, not to the Empire, but to the Popedum: &amp; deuise such statelie
    						designes, to inuest the bishop of Roome, The vniuersal monarch of the World? = 
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<location name="Rome"/>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    				<position book_orientation="270" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						= Aspiring to a greater maiestie, then euer Alexander the Great, or greater Cesar
    						vsurped. Do you not think them holie preists, that can platforme Such [p. 350: gallant conceits for their owne supremacie, &amp; the pompe of spiritual pastors: the notablest fooles-paradise in the World. Basta.]
    						<!-- Continues onto facing page, right margin, Ha2.015v -->
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<person name="Alexander the Great"/>
